modules.description: This module handles MP4 container operations for AAC decoding, providing functions to open files, identify AAC tracks, and manage sample reading. It works with file descriptors, tracks, and audio samples, supporting precise seeking and metadata extraction. Concrete uses include initializing decoders for specific tracks, decoding audio samples into float arrays, and retrieving MP4 metadata tags.

This module decodes AAC and AAC+ audio streams, offering functions to initialize a decoder, decode frames into PCM samples, and reset decoding state. The core type `t` represents decoder state, and operations like `decode` process byte buffers into channel-specific audio data. A child module extends this functionality to MP4 containers, enabling track identification, sample reading, and metadata extraction. Together, they support use cases like initializing decoders for specific MP4 tracks, seeking precisely within audio files, and converting raw AAC bitstreams into playable float arrays.
